    <title>Edit Product</title>
    <meta charset="utf-8">

  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Edit Product</h1>
    <h2>Basic Path</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><p>Include "View Products".</p></li>
      <li><p>The Inventory Manager selects one of the products to edit.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software retrieves the available vendors.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software retrieves the available departments.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software retrieves the available unit types.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software retrieves the information about the selected product.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software uses the retrieved information as defaults.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts the Inventory Manager for the product's UPC.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the product's description, price per item, cost
	  per ordering unit, par, ordering units, economic ordering unit, vendor,
	  category id, item #, default unit type, primary par, and secondary par.</p></li>
      <li><p>If an EOQ is not entered but an order by units is, then the EOQ is the by default the
	  same values as that of the order by units.</p></li>
      <li><p>The Inventory Manager enters values for the above prompts.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the UPC is either unique or empty.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the item number is eithe4r unique or empty.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the UPC is a valid UPC.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the description is unique and non-empty.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the order by units is non-empty, positive, integer.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the par is a non-empty integer, greater than 0.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the eoq is a non-empty integer, greater than 0.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the case pack is a non-empty integer, greater than 0.</p></li>
      <li><p>With the entered values, the software creates a new product.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software updates the product persistently.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software updates any listing of the updated product.</p></li>
      

	  
    <h2>Alternate Paths</h2>
    <h3>DB Error</h3>
  </body>

</html>
